Sentencas: Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3 (YST) was synthesized and the performance of a YST-CeO2 composite as an alternative anode for the direct Utilization of CH4 in Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) was investigated.
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction showed that YST had good chemical compatibility with CeO2 and YSZ (8 mol% Y-doped ZrO2).
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel

Sentencas: The shrinkage of the YST-CeO2 composite oil sintering was less than that of pure YSZ and CeO2, and its thermal-expansion behavior was similar to that of YSZ.
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel

Sentencas: With YSZ as electrolyte, ScSZ (10 mol% Sc-doped ZrO2)-LSM (La0.8Sr0.2MnO3) as cathode, and YST-CeO2 composite as anode, single cells were prepared and tested in both H-2 and CH4.
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel

Sentencas: The maximum power density obtained at 900 degrees C was 161.7 mW cm(-2) in H-2 atmosphere and 141.3 mW cm(-2) in CH4.
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel

Sentencas: The results demonstrated the potential of using YST-CeO2 composite as the anode for SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of Sr0.88Y0.08TiO3-CeO2 as composite anode for solid oxide fuel cells running on CH4 fuel
